<body>
    <Header />
<main>
        <!-- Hero -->
        <section class="service-page-hero">
            <p
                style="color:var(--accent-gold-dark); font-size:0.9rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:2px; margin-bottom:1rem;">
                Meet Your Lawyer</p>
            <h1 class="hero-title">Meet Advocate <span class="text-gradient">Reema Jawed</span></h1>
            <p class="hero-subtitle" style="margin:0 auto; max-width:800px;">The female family lawyer behind MR Law
                Associates, and the caring, confidential approach she brings to divorce, khula, custody, maintenance and
                dower for women in Karachi.</p>
            <p style="color:var(--text-secondary); font-size:0.85rem; margin-top:1rem;">Verified Practice Profile |
                Enrolled with Sindh Bar Council</p>
            <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">›</span> <span class="current">About MR Law Associates</span></nav>
        </section>

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <div class="service-page-content about-page">
            <article class="service-main">

                <!-- Advocate Profile Card -->
                <div class="about-profile-card reveal">
                    <h2 class="profile-name">Reema Jawed</h2>
                    <h3 class="profile-title">Advocate High Court, Karachi</h3>
                    <p class="profile-bio speakable-intro"><strong>Reema Jawed is a female Advocate High Court in
                            Karachi</strong> and the founder of MR Law Associates. With years of family-law experience
                        before Karachi's Family Courts and the High Court of Sindh, she gives women caring, confidential
                        help with divorce, khula, child custody, maintenance, dower, and protection from domestic
                        violence.</p>

                    <div class="about-credentials">
                        <div class="about-credential">
                            <h4>Professional Standing</h4>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Enrolled Advocate, Sindh Bar Council</li>
                                <li>Member, Sindh High Court Bar Association</li>
                                <li>Member, Karachi Bar Association</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div class="about-credential">
                            <h4>Primary Jurisdictions</h4>
                            <ul>
                                <li>High Court of Sindh (Family Appeals)</li>
                                <li>Karachi Family Courts</li>
                                <li>Guardian Courts (Custody & Guardianship)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Stats -->
                <div class="about-stats">
                    <div class="about-stat reveal">
                        <span class="stat-number">500+</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Family Cases</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="about-stat reveal">
                        <span class="stat-number">14+</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Years Experience</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="about-stat reveal">
                        <span class="stat-number">4.9</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Client Rating</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="about-stat reveal">
                        <span class="stat-number">100%</span>
                        <span class="stat-label">Confidential</span>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr class="about-divider">

                <!-- Philosophy Section -->
                <h2>The MR Law Associates Philosophy</h2>
                <p class="about-section-subtitle">We built MR Law Associates on three simple promises to the women and families who trust us with their most
                    personal matters.</p>

                <div class="about-values-grid">
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Caring, Steady Guidance</h3>
                        <p>We never let your case drift. From the first call to the final order, we keep things moving,
                            explain each step in plain words, and carry the legal weight so you do not have to.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Complete Confidentiality</h3>
                        <p>Family matters are deeply personal. Everything you share stays private, and a female advocate
                            handles your <a href="/services/family-lawyer/" style="color:var(--accent-gold-dark);">case</a>
                            with the sensitivity it deserves. Where it is safe, we settle with dignity; where it is not,
                            we protect you firmly in court.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Everything Done Properly</h3>
                        <p>Litigation is only half our work. We guide you through the full family law process, drafting airtight nikah nama and settlement documents, preparing court applications correctly, and organising your evidence so problems are prevented before they ever reach the courtroom.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr class="about-divider">

                <!-- Practice Areas -->
                <h2>Our Practice Areas</h2>
                <p class="about-section-subtitle">MR Law Associates focuses only on family law. These are the matters we handle every day for women and families
                    in Karachi.</p>

                <div class="about-practice-grid">
                    <a href="/services/family-lawyer/" class="about-practice-item">
                        Family Law
                    </a>
                    <a href="/services/divorce-custody-case/" class="about-practice-item">
                        Divorce (Talaq)
                    </a>
                    <a href="/services/khula-procedure/" class="about-practice-item">
                        Khula
                    </a>
                    <a href="/services/child-custody-lawyer/" class="about-practice-item">
                        Child Custody
                    </a>
                    <a href="/services/court-marriage-lawyer/" class="about-practice-item">
                        Court Marriage
                    </a>
                    <a href="/services/maintenance-alimony-lawyer/" class="about-practice-item">
                        Maintenance
                    </a>
                    <a href="/services/dower-haq-mehr-recovery/" class="about-practice-item">
                        Dower &amp; Dowry
                    </a>
                    <a href="/services/guardianship-certificate-lawyer/" class="about-practice-item">
                        Guardianship
                    </a>
                </div>
                </div>

                <hr class="about-divider">

                <!-- Office Location -->
                <h2>Our Office</h2>
                <p class="about-section-subtitle">MR Law Associates is conveniently located within walking distance of
                    the Karachi City Courts complex.</p>

                <div class="service-features" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Office Address</h3>
                        <p>Suite # 504, 5th Floor<br>
                            Tahir Plaza, Near City Court<br>
                            Karachi, Pakistan</p>
                        <p style="margin-top:1rem;"><strong>Hours:</strong> Monday to Saturday, 10:00 AM to 6:00 PM</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Contact Information</h3>
                        <p><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:03363120798"
                                style="color:var(--accent-gold-dark);">0336 3120798</a><br>
                            <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:info@mrlawassociates.com"
                                style="color:var(--accent-gold-dark);">info@mrlawassociates.com</a>
                        </p>
                        <p style="margin-top:1rem;"><strong>WhatsApp:</strong> <a href="https://wa.me/923363120798"
                                style="color:var(--accent-gold-dark);" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Send a
                                message</a></p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <hr class="about-divider">

                <!-- FAQ Section -->
                <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Our Practice</h2>

                <div class="service-features" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Which courts do you handle family cases in?</h3>
                        <p>We appear before the <strong>Family Courts and Guardian Courts</strong> in Karachi, and the
                            <strong>High Court of Sindh</strong> where a family matter needs an appeal. Our office sits
                            beside the City Court complex, so filings and hearings move quickly.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Why choose a female family lawyer?</h3>
                        <p>Many women feel more comfortable sharing sensitive matters with another woman. Advocate Reema
                            Jawed handles your case personally, with warmth and <strong>complete confidentiality</strong>,
                            and as an Advocate High Court she can take your matter through appeal if needed.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Do you handle overseas Pakistani cases?</h3>
                        <p><strong>Yes.</strong> Through a Special Power of Attorney, we represent overseas Pakistanis in the Gulf, the UK, and North America for divorce, khula, child custody, and maintenance, without requiring you to fly back for hearings.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>What is your approach to family law?</h3>
                        <p>We lead with calm, caring guidance and try to resolve matters with dignity, especially where
                            children are involved. When the other side will not cooperate or there is abuse, we protect
                            your rights <strong>firmly in court</strong>, and everything stays confidential.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Do you only practise family law?</h3>
                        <p><strong>Yes.</strong> MR Law Associates focuses only on family law, so divorce, khula,
                            custody, maintenance, dower, guardianship, and protection from domestic violence are what we
                            do every day. That focus means deep, current experience in your kind of case.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="feature-box reveal">
                        <h3>Where is your office located?</h3>
                        <p>Suite # 504, 5th Floor, Tahir Plaza, Near City Court, Karachi. We are located <strong>within
                                walking distance</strong> of the Karachi City Courts complex for convenient court
                            appearances and client meetings.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- CTA -->
                <div class="about-cta reveal">
                    <h2>Ready to Talk About Your Family Matter?</h2>
                    <p>Whether it is divorce, khula, custody, maintenance, or protection from an unsafe situation, talk
                        to Advocate Reema Jawed for caring, confidential guidance, with no pressure.</p>
                    <div class="cta-buttons">
                        <a href="tel:03363120798" class="btn btn-primary">Call: 0336 3120798</a>
                        <a href="https://wa.me/923363120798" class="btn btn-secondary" target="_blank"
                            rel="noopener">WhatsApp</a>
                        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-outline">Schedule Consultation</a>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Disclaimer -->
                <p
                    style="color:var(--text-secondary); font-size:0.8rem; margin-top:2rem; padding-top:1.5rem; border-top:1px solid var(--border-glass); text-align:center; line-height:1.6;">
                    <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> The information on this page does not constitute legal advice. Past
                    litigation success does not guarantee future case outcomes as every matter depends on unique factual
                    circumstances. Representation is established only upon signing a Vakalatnama. MR Law Associates
                    practices in Karachi, Pakistan.
                </p>

            </article>
        </div>
    </main>

    <Footer />
    <script is:inline src="/script.js"></script>
</body>

</html>